JVM Language Shootout
I am using this project to compare various JVM languages, including Clojure, Fan, Groovy, Ruby, and Scala. 
Stuart Halloway
stu AT think relevance DOT com

Common ground between the languages:
* everything is an object
* convenient operators
* convenient Strings
* runtime type safety
* convenient Arrays
* convenient Maps
* functional arguments / closures
* ranges
* everything returns a value
* object-oriented case statements
* low-ceremony property definitions
* roll-your-own constructs
* helpful exceptions
* relaxed syntax

Unique features:
* Ruby metaprogramming
* Ruby modules
* Clojure macros
* Clojure STM
* Clojure multiple dispatch
* Clojure type hints
* Scala implicit coercion
* Scala for expressions
* Scala pattern matching
* Scala traits
* Scala Vars and vals

Other topics
* Coding without side effects


